==Current use==

After closure as an operational airfield in 1966, the airfield became the home of the [[Construction Industry Training Board]]. The runways have gone, but the majority of buildings on the site, including some hangars and the control tower, remain in use by the CITB.<ref>[http://airfieldarchaeology.fotopic.net/c1495033.html Airfield Archeology - Bircham Newton]</ref>The control tower was demolished in 2010 due to its poor condition.<ref name="CT"/>

Constructionarium is also based within the estate, providing a week's practical learning opportunity for undergraduates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.constructionarium.co.uk/pages/where-is-it-held.php|title=Where is it held|publisher=Constructionarium|accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref>

